The Federal Government has reached an agreement with South-West governors on Western Nigerian Security Outfit code-named Operation Amotekun. Senior Special Assistant to the Vice-President, Laolu Akande, disclosed this on his Twitter handle on Thursday. However, he did not give details of the agreement reached. Osinbajo and the governors of the South-West states have been met at the Presidential Villa in Abuja on Thursday. It was gathered top on the agenda was Amotekun, which the federal government has declared as illegal. Details shortly… News Flash: FG, Southwest Governors agree on Amotekun — Laolu Akande (@akandeoj) January 23, 2020  